conversations.content: Please create a new 1 hour long event 'Follow-up meeting' on 2024-05-19 at 10:00 or 16:00 if at 10:00 I already have something. The description should be 'Follow-up meeting to discuss the project.'. The event should have the same participants as 'Introductory meeting' event on 2024-05-15.

(function_thought)
To create the new event, I need to first check the existing calendar events on the specified date of 2024-05-19. I will check if there are any conflicts at 10:00 and if there are any participants from the "Introductory meeting" event on 2024-05-15. The first step will be to search for the "Introductory meeting" events to retrieve participants and then check the calendar for events on 2024-05-19. 
</function_thought>

(function_call)
[search_calendar_events(query="Introductory meeting"), get_day_calendar_events(day="2024-05-19")]
</function_call>
